      "message": "Most of the APIs look like the ID that was passed in with the request (node_id in this case) is passed back in the reply. That seems unnecessary. The context field exists to match a reply to a corresponding request that was sent.\n\nOr is there some other use for node_id in the reply? Will it ever be different than the value of node_id from the request? If you\u0027re just passing back a value verbatim that was provided in the request, its not needed. You could probably eliminate the reply definition and declare the request as \"autoreply\" in any similar cases.",
      "revId": "5df859cdda4cbe16ca00b72309d3efb964cb574f",
