      "message": "All of these functions like tm_sys_node_add(), tm_sys_node_suspend(), etc return 0 unconditionally. The callbacks being invoked (node_add, node_suspend, etc) have an integer return value. I presume that it might be possible for the callbacks to fail. Why not return the value returned by the callback?\n\nI also think that you should check if dev_class-\u003etm_sys_impl is null and return VNET_API_ERR_UNIMPLEMENTED if that\u0027s true before trying to invoke one of the callbacks.",
